In[8]:
# 4. Clean the text and remove stopwords
def clean_text(text):
    text = re.sub(r"http\S+", "", text)
    text = re.sub(r"[^a-zA-Z\s]", "", text)
    text = text.lower()
    words = text.split()
    words = [word for word in words if word not in stop_words]
    return " ".join(words)
df["Cleaned_Comment"] = df["Comment"].apply(clean_text)

# 5. Apply TextBlob sentiment analysis
df["Polarity"] = df["Cleaned_Comment"].apply(lambda x: TextBlob(x).sentiment.polarity)
df["Subjectivity"] = df["Cleaned_Comment"].apply(lambda x: TextBlob(x).sentiment.subjectivity)
df["Sentiment"] = df["Polarity"].apply(
    lambda x: "positive" if x > 0 else ("negative" if x < 0 else "neutral")
)
# Print sentiment counts
print("Sentiment Counts:")
print(df["Sentiment"].value_counts())

# 6. Sentiment distribution barplot
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
sns.countplot(data=df, x="Sentiment", palette="coolwarm")
plt.title("Sentiment Distribution of Visit Rwanda Comments")
plt.xlabel("Sentiment")
plt.ylabel("Number of Comments")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 8. Scatter Plot: Polarity vs Subjectivity
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df, x="Polarity", y="Subjectivity", hue="Sentiment", palette="coolwarm", alpha=0.6)
plt.title("Polarity vs Subjectivity of Visit Rwanda Comments")
plt.xlabel("Polarity (Negative to Positive)")
plt.ylabel("Subjectivity (Objective to Subjective)")
plt.axvline(0, color='gray', linestyle='--')
plt.axhline(0.5, color='gray', linestyle='--')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
In[11]:
# 7. WordClouds by Sentiment Category
combined_stopwords = stop_words.union(STOPWORDS)
fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 6))

for i, sentiment in enumerate(['positive', 'neutral', 'negative']):
    text = ' '.join(df[df['Sentiment'] == sentiment]['Cleaned_Comment'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=600, height=400, background_color='white',
                          stopwords=combined_stopwords, colormap='plasma').generate(text)
    axs[i].imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    axs[i].axis('off')
    axs[i].set_title(f'{sentiment.capitalize()} Comments Word Cloud')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
